Food_Name: Mosa
Ingredients: Overripe plantains
1 egg
Flour (as needed for binding)
Sugar (optional, to taste)
Salt to taste
Oil for frying
Procedures: Mash the plantains until smooth. Mix in the egg, a bit of flour, sugar, and salt until you have a thick batter.
Heat oil in a deep fryer.
Spoon dollops of the batter into the hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve warm.